entry.title: Gaza's Al-Shifa Hospital Crippled as Israeli Forces Move Closer
entry.content: Hospital officials said doctors were using scant remaining medical supplies as the facility largely operated without electricity and water ran desperately low.

entry.title: The Militia at the Center of the Darfur Genocide Kills Hundreds in Sudan
entry.content: A paramilitary group that grew from the infamous Janjaweed militia has been blamed for the killing of about 800 people, mostly boys and men, in a Darfur refugee camp.

entry.title: India, China Fight for Influence Over Tiny Archipelago Nation
entry.content: The fierce rivalry between the Asian powers is on display in the Maldives, better known for its white sand beaches and crystal clear waters than as a strategic military outpost.

entry.title: As Chinese Tastes Change, Farmers Everywhere Rip Up and Replant
entry.content: The windfall is transforming entire regions, but some are starting to worry: What if China stops buying?
